Przyimków miejsca używamy w zdaniach, które opisują, gdzie coś się znajduje. Są to m.in.:
on- na,
under- pod,
in front of - przed,
behind - za,
beside/next to - obok,
near- w pobliżu,
at- przy,
in - w,
between - pomiędzy,
among- pomiędzy
Between używamy by powiedzieć,
że coś znajduje się pomiędzy dwiema rzeczami lub osobami, natomiast among określa położenie pomiędzy większą liczbą rzeczy bądź ludzi.

The vase is on the table.
- Wazon jest na stole.
The cat is under the table.
- Kot jest pod stołem.

Tom is in front of Paul.
- Tom jest przed Poulem.
Paul is behind Tom.
- Paul jest za Tomem.

The armchair is beside/next to the
fireplace. - Fotel znajduje się obok kominka.
The lamp is near the fireplace.
- Lompa znajduje się w pobliżu kominka.

The man is at the door.
- Mężczyzna stoi przy drzwiach.
The children are in the room.
- Dzieci są w pokoju.

The house is between the bank
and the post office
- Dom znajduje się pomiędzy
bankiem a pocztą.

The teacher is standing among
the students.
- Nauczyciel stoi pomiędzy
uczniami/wsród uczniów.

AT używamy w wyrażeniach:
at school - w szkole,
at university - na uniwersytecie,
at college - na uniwersytecie,
at work - w pracy,
at home - w domu,
at the top of ... - na górze ... ,
at the bottom of .. - na dole ...
♦ przy podawaniu numeru domu w adresach:
at 20, Oxford Street- pod numerem 20 przy Oxford Street
ALE: in Oxford Street- przy Oxford Street

IN używamy w wyrażeniach:
in the middle- w środku,
in the air- w powietrzu,
in the sky - na niebie,
in bed - w łóżku, in hospital - w szpitalu,
in prison - w więzieniu,
in a newspaper/ magazine - w gazecie/ czasopiśmie,
in a picture - na obrazku.
♦ z nazwami miast, państw i kontynentów:
in Athens - w Atenach,
in Britain - w Wielkiej Brytanii,
in Europe - w Europie,
in Australia- w Australii.

ON używamy w wyrażeniach:
on the left - na lewo, po lewej stronie,
on the right - na prawo, po prawej stronie,
on the first/second floor - na pierwszym/drugim piętrze.

Mówimy: on the chair- na krześle,
ALE: in the armchair- w fotelu.

ćwiczenie 5
wstaw in, at lub on
1 What have you got [...] your pocket?
2 Where's Paul? He is [...] his bedroom.
3 Mother is [...] home.
4 I like to sit [...] an armchair by the fire.
5 Glasgow is a large city [...] Scotland.
6 We live [...] number 37, King's Road.
7 The answer is [...] the bottom of the page.
8 My house is the first one [...] the left.
9 She has left her purse [...] the chair.
10 The manager's office is [...] the second floor.
11 Dinner is [...] the table.
12 Paul is [...] hospital because he is ill.
1 in
2 in 5 1n 8 on
3 at 6 at 9 on
4 1n 7 at 10 on
11 on
12 in

ćwiczenie 6
Podkreśl właściwe przyimki.
1 I'm studying French [on/in/at] school.
2 Your shoes are [under/between/at] the bed.
3 The cat is lying [among/in front of/at] the fire.
4 Sue is standing [under /at/behind] Nancy.
5 The boy is standing [on/in/among] his friends.
6 Who was that woman [beside/under/on] your mother?
7 Our house is [among/near /in] the fire station.
8 He has a computer [in front of/on/at] his desk.
9 The children are playing [at/on/in] the garden.
10 The sofa is [at/next to/among] the table.
11 I sit [at/in/between] my two best friends in class.
12 George studied History [in/on/at] the University of Essex.
1 at
2 under 6 beside
3 in front of
4 behind
5 among
7 near
8 on
9 in
10 next to
11 between
12 at

ćwiczenie 7
Wstaw przyimki z listy near, on, at, in front of in
Dear Sally,
My family and I are (1)[...] New York. We are s pending the Christmas holidays with our relatives.
We are staying (2) [...] my uncle's house. I'm
having a lot of fun with my cousins. There is a park (3) [...] their house. We play (4) [...] the
swings and slides every day.
There was a snowstorm yesterday! There is a lot of
snow (5) [...] the ground now. My cousins and
I want to make a snowman (6) [...] the house.
I hope you had a good time (7) [...] Italy.
Write soon.
Love,
Janet
